# I made this to test markdown rendering when making the website. Congrats on finding it 🎉

## Headings

### H3 Heading
#### H4 Heading
##### H5 Heading
###### H6 Heading

## Text Formatting

This is **bold**, this is *italic*, this is ***bold italic***, this is ~~strikethrough~~, and this is `inline code`.

Here's a [link](https://example.com) and an autolink: https://example.com

## Blockquotes

> This is a regular blockquote.
>
> It can span multiple paragraphs.

> Nested blockquote:
>> This is nested inside.

## Callouts

> [!NOTE] A Note
> This is a note callout with some **bold** and *italic* text.

> [!TIP] Helpful Tip
> This is a tip callout.

> [!WARNING] Be Careful
> This is a warning callout.

> [!DANGER] Danger Zone
> This is a danger callout.

> [!INFO] For Your Information
> This is an info callout.

> [!IMPORTANT] Important
> This is an important callout.

> [!CAUTION] Proceed with Caution
> This is a caution callout.

## Lists

### Unordered
- Item one
- Item two
  - Nested item
  - Another nested item
    - Deep nested
- Item three

### Ordered
1. First
2. Second
3. Third
   1. Sub-item
   2. Sub-item

### Task List (GFM)
- [x] Completed task
- [ ] Incomplete task
- [x] Another done task

## Code Blocks

```javascript
function greet(name) {
  console.log("Hello, " + name + "!");
  return { greeting: true };
}
```

```rust
fn main() {
    let x: i32 = 42;
    println!("The answer is {}", x);
}
```

```python
def fibonacci(n):
    if n <= 1:
        return n
    return fibonacci(n - 1) + fibonacci(n - 2)
```

```bash
curl -s https://api.example.com/data | jq '.results[]'
```

